  <header>
    <h1>How to Make a Web Portal for Businesses to Deliver Products</h1>
    <p>A complete guide to creating a delivery management web portal for businesses to sell and deliver products online.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Why Create a Web Portal for Product Delivery?</h2>
    <p>Businesses today rely heavily on digital platforms to connect with customers. A dedicated web portal helps you:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Manage online product orders efficiently</li>
      <li>Track deliveries and logistics in real time</li>
      <li>Provide secure online payments</li>
      <li>Enhance customer satisfaction with better service</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Steps to Build a Product Delivery Web Portal</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Step 1: Define Business Requirements</strong> – Decide whether your portal is for grocery, retail, or B2B product delivery.</li>
      <li><strong>Step 2: Choose the Right Technology</strong> – Use frameworks like Laravel, Node.js, Django, or ready-made platforms.</li>
      <li><strong>Step 3: Core Features</strong> – User registration, product catalog, cart & checkout, delivery tracking, and payment gateway integration.</li>
      <li><strong>Step 4: Design User-Friendly UI</strong> – Make navigation simple and mobile-friendly.</li>
      <li><strong>Step 5: Integrate Delivery Management</strong> – GPS tracking, route optimization, and automated dispatch.</li>
      <li><strong>Step 6: Test and Launch</strong> – Perform security, load, and UX testing before going live.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

